
Depression, with around 263 million patients world wide and anxiety disorder are the two most prevalent. They both tend to rely on environmental stressors and are therefore more prevalent in crowded cities or stressful jobs, supporting the gene activation being controlled by environmental factors. Women in general are more diagnoses with depression both because they seek out help and because they are prone to post-natal depression. And have shifts associated with mentral cycles, supporting biological and chromosomal basis. Finally, diagnosis occur in early 20’s to late 40’s maybe this is tied to more stress but also the need for developed pre frontal cortices for certain symptoms.
 


